  <section xml:id="sec-assessments">
    <title>Assessments</title>
    <paragraphs>
      <title>Participation and Attendance</title>
      <p>
        This is an in-person course and you are expected to attend all class session (unless you are sick in which case you should email me to let me know).  In addition to lectures, class time will be used for group work and in-class exercises.  This is one of the best ways to get practice with the type of problems that will be on the exams.
      </p>
      <p>
          Another component of your participation grade is office hours.  If you are struggling with any of the material, it is your responsibility to come to office hours so I can help clarify things. <em>If you come to office hours at least once in the first 4 weeks you will receive an extra point in the participation component of your grade.</em> 
      </p>
    </paragraphs>
    <paragraphs>
      <title>Homework</title>
      <p>
        The bulk of your grade in the class will be from webwork.  See the link above for how to log in to the webwork system. Homeworks will usually be due on Mondays, and will be roughly every week.  
      </p>
    </paragraphs>
    <paragraphs>
      <title>Exams</title>
      <p>
        This course will have two midterms and a final exam. The questions will be similar to questions you have seen on homeworks or in class.  The dates and times for these assessments are:
        <dl>
          <li>
            <title>Midterm I</title>
            <p>
              Friday, September 26, 2025. In class.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <title>Midterm II</title>
            <p>
              Friday, October 31, 2025. In class.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <title>Final Exam</title>
            <p>
              The final will occur on the <alert>Wednesday</alert> of finals week, 4:10-6:10 pm in our usual classroom.
            </p>
          </li>
        </dl>
      </p>
      <p>
        During exams, you will not be allowed to use any electronic devices. You will be allowed bring a one-page sheet of notes which you can write yourself before the exam.
      </p>
    </paragraphs>
  </section>
